headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo scored an NBA season-high 54 points, but committed two turnovers after Tyrese Haliburton’s go-ahead 3-pointer with 1:29 left and the Indiana Pacers beat the Milwaukee Bucks 126-124 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Giannis Antetokounmpo scores 54 points, but Haliburton, Pacers rally for 126-124 win over Bucks

headlines.description: — Trae Young put on a show for nearly 20,000 fans in the NBA's regular-season game in Mexico City.
headlines.shortLinkText: Young scores 41, Murray hits go-ahead 3 as the Hawks beat the Magic 120-119 in Mexico City
